spans.text: mid air move slow and silently
mid air move slow and silently
the first utterance of thy deep voice
over boggy moor or swampy plain , A streaming cataract of flame
pours A general blaze , and from the war of clouds , Red , writhing falls the embodied bolt of heaven
Like the upbreaking of a ruined world , In awful majesty the explosion bursts Wide and astounding over the trembling land
bursts Wide and astounding over the trembling land
Huge fragments of the rugged steep
bend that never bent before , The stoutest hearts begin to fail , And many a manly face is pale
The palsied action of their minds
gleam , And through the rent cloud , silvered with his rays , The sun on all this wild affray looks down , As , high enthroned above all mortal ken , A higher Power beholds the strife of men
